<p><strong>2. Shorter Loan Tenure:</strong> While a 30-year tenure gives you a comfortably low monthly EMI, it drastically increases your total interest outgo. If your monthly budget permits, always opt for a 15 or 20-year tenure. The slightly higher EMI will save you lakhs in interest payments.</p>
